Bad biting flies had to leave. Saw sunfish and pilot whales. Millions of dead jellies. Dolphins x 2
Great time in this beautiful town, awesome charcuterie, hike to church and fort not great. Olivers restaurant amazing. Saw waiter in store next day.
Saw fin whale, rolly night, had to leave before 5, almost rolled out of bed
Amazing sunset with the rock. A little bouncy but not bad. Great Udon noodles.
Some of the best pizza at O'Pagnottiello. Friendly old fisherman allowed us to moor next to them. Dumped a lot of trash. Very authentic old town.

Epic drone footage, beautiful rock formation and cliffs. Woke up with anchor alarm blearing, a little too close to another boat, not sure if we dragged, but we upped and left just after 5am - good thing too, we did not know the long day ahead
Looong day, anchorages planned in Capri and others did not look good so we pushed through. What a great decision! Bucket list item, anchored outside Atrani, spectacular.

Moved into the marina. Met Giulio, what a character. Mob? Almost left, shall we say a spirited discussion? It all worked out in the end, first few nights were amazing, birthday day was incredible. Scooter ride to Ravello, amazing dinner at Gemma, a gem. Great dinner on the 14th from amazing restaurant with a view of Doublestar. Walked into Atrani. Thursday the weather turned and we had the 1:20 scooter ride for blood tests and ECG. Wonderful people at the clinic, 'Francesca' - 5' of smiles. Bad night, lots of swell, and then a lot of wind Friday. Leaving Saturday with cross wind was stressful, but the cash in had Giulio pushed with his dinghy and we were fine.
Got in at sunset, a little rolly but not too bad. Pretty spot. Left early. Tanya did not sleep a wink - night 3 of no booze behind us.
